The paper deals with mechanism design, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT) and economics (cs.EC). The problem involves designing mechanisms to maximize social welfare, which is a common goal in algorithmic game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of approximation guarantees suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the subfield of theoretical computer science (cs.DS). Finally, the analysis of randomized mechanisms suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG).
